13/01/2006
PODGORICA, Serbia-Montenegro -- The EU has sent envoy Miroslav Lajcak to Montenegro to discuss the upcoming independence referendum with local leaders.
Lajcak on Thursday (12 January) met with representatives of the opposition who want to retain the union with Serbia.
He is also due to hold talks with Prime Minister Milo Djukanovic and other pro-independence officials to discuss the conditions under which the vote would take place.
(RFE/RL - 12/01/06)
